snippet.textDisplay: I have two questions.  First, won't the plasma cutter cut right through the mesh on the table, and, if you're not careful, the structure of the table itself?  Second, sometimes you weld things, and sometimes you bolt things together.  I know that often it's a matter of not being able to get the bench welder to the object (like the angle brace you put on the slip roller), but other times you do some welding at the bench, and then bolt something to what you just welded, right there (like when you attached the wheels to the new leg of the slip roller).  Why one over the other?
